body.p:
You can set the:
Show profiling attribute name option - if checked, the conditional text markers represent a list of attribute names and their currently set values. If you uncheck this option, only the values are presented.
Background color - specifies the color used in the Author mode to render the background color of the conditional text markers;
Attribute name foreground color - specifies the foreground color used in the Author mode to render the profiling attributes name in the conditional text markers;
Attribute values foreground color - specifies the foreground color used in the Author mode to render the profiling attributes values in the conditional text markers;
Border color - specifies the color of the border used in the Author mode to decorate the conditional text blocks.
